{
  "texts": [
    "Larger LMs generally demonstrate better performance, with UnifiedQA using T5-3B leading, yet struggling with metaphors and counterfactual situations.",
    "Complementing this, BrainTeaser (Jiang et al., 2023) introduces 1119 lateral thinking puzzles.",
    "It contrasts instruction-based models (ChatGPT, T0, and FlanT5 (Chung et al., 2022)) with commonsense ones (including RoBERTa variants and CAR (Wang et al., 2023c)).",
    "ChatGPT excels in both sentence-based and word-based puzzles, indicating its strength in lateral thinking.",
    "However, overall, LLMs still face challenges in exhibiting lateral thinking, with common errors in memorization and commonsense association."
  ]
}